#=
Global variables are automatically hidden by assignment to an undeclared variable of the same name within a function 
when running a program outside the Julia REPL (Julia's command line interactive mode) but this behavior does not occur inside the REPL.

For example:

=#

r = 0

function areacircle(radius)
    r = pi * radius * radius
end

println("r is $r")

#+
Inside the REPL, the with above Julia prints 

If the above is placed in a text file and run as a script, Julia prints

